1. PURPOSE
This System Architecture Document (SAD) describes the complete technical architecture of the Golden Governor v1.2.5 Lite safety kernel and the Voltr Vault Manager off‑chain orchestrator. It explains how the system enforces a hard 15% maximum drawdown, validates trades, executes fallback liquidation, and maintains deterministic behavior under adversarial conditions.

2. SYSTEM OVERVIEW
The system consists of two cooperating components:

2.1 On‑Chain Component — Golden Governor v1.2.5 Lite
- Enforces 10 independent safety envelopes
- Enforces a hard 15% drawdown cap
- Validates every trade against oracle, MEV, leverage, exposure, and timing rules
- Maintains a mode ladder (Normal → Degraded → Recovering → Lockout)
- Performs Phoenix Restart after a 2‑hour cooldown
- Rejects stale or manipulated oracle data
- Detects integrity tampering via ZT Lite hash folding

2.2 Off‑Chain Component — Voltr Vault Manager
- Computes daily yield from 18 strategies
- Adjusts leverage based on governor mode
- Submits trades through the governor
- Implements fallback liquidation at 85% of the drawdown envelope
- Re‑enters positions after Phoenix cooldown using risk‑reduction logic
- Calls risk_tick() before every trade to satisfy the 3‑second safety window

